spec: as3406
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 674 (as3406): __bool__, __str__, __repr__ dict-presence checks for asyncio types."
    - "Theme: __bool__/__str__/__repr__ dict-presence (bool(x), str(x), repr(x))."
    - "All values False — asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives with no custom bool/str/repr defined in their own __dict__."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.PriorityQueue, asyncio.LifoQueue."
    - "Key finding (__bool__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __bool__. bool() delegates to __bool__ (truth-value testing protocol) when defined on the class's own __dict__. asyncio types define no truth-value protocol in their own __dict__ — bool(task), bool(event), bool(queue) are not meaningful Python expressions that correspond to an overridden __bool__. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: these are boolean-state guards but is_set()/locked() are methods, not the __bool__ slot. asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: the permit counter is encapsulated; no __bool__ is defined in the class __dict__. asyncio.Task/Future: pending coroutine result handles with no truth-value semantics in their own __dict__. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __bool__ defined at the class level."
    - "Key finding (__str__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __str__. str() delegates to __str__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. asyncio types rely on inherited __str__ from object — none of the 10 classes define a custom __str__ in their own __dict__. The string representation of asyncio primitives falls back to the default object repr. asyncio.Task and asyncio.Future do expose useful repr() via __repr__, but __str__ is inherited, not overridden in their own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__repr__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __repr__. repr() delegates to __repr__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. While asyncio.Task and asyncio.Future do produce informative repr strings at runtime, CPython implements these via C-level tp_repr slots — not via a Python-level __repr__ entry in the class's __dict__. As a result, operator.contains(asyncio.Task.__dict__, '__repr__') and operator.contains(asyncio.Future.__dict__, '__repr__') both return false."
    - "Continues the all-false run from wave 656 (__call__/__len__/__getitem__) through wave 674 (__bool__/__str__/__repr__) — nineteen consecutive waves of 100% false results for asyncio types."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 660 (as3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 661 (as3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 662 (as3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 664 (as3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 665 (as3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 666 (as3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 667 (as3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 668 (as3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 669 (as3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 670 (as3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 671 (as3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 672 (as3376): __trunc__/__round__/__index__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 673 (as3391): __int__/__float__/__complex__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 674 (as3406): __bool__/__str__/__repr__ — all false for all 10."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __bool__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__bool__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __bool__.
# bool() delegates to __bool__ (truth-value testing protocol) when defined
#   in the class's own __dict__.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization guards with
#   is_set()/locked() methods, but no __bool__ entry in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: the permit counter is encapsulated
#   behind acquire()/release() coroutines; no __bool__ is in their __dict__.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles with no truth-value protocol
#   defined in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __bool__ defined
#   at the class level in their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

